The paper discusses the use of visualization techniques and a NoSQL database to analyze scholarly article data from various journals. This falls under the domain of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as the paper deals with extracting and analyzing data from a repository of scholarly articles. The use of a graph database also suggests the involvement of database systems (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper mentions the detection of cartel behavior, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) or security and privacy (cs.SD).
